{"cells":[{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"# Lesson 2: Render Map ","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"In this lesson, you will create a page, connect it to a route, and then render a map using a map provider like Leaflet.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Learning Objectives","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"After completing this lesson, you will be able to:\n- Import external libraries into your application.\n- Create a page.\n- Create a route to the page.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Estimated time ","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"This lab will take approximately **15 minutes** to complete.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Lab Support","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"For support, check out the <a href=\"https://learn.c3.ai/page/help-center\" target=\"_blank\">Help Center</a> for  information.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Prerequisites","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Install the required libraries for building this application by following the example notebook located at \n<a href='./01-import-libraries.c3nb'><code>01-import-libraries.c3nb</code></a>","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"-----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Part 1: Create a home page","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"It's time to create a new page. All custom React pages must be defined under <code>ui/c3/src/customInstances/</code>.\n\nCreate the `customInstances` folder under `ui/c3/src`. In the new folder, create a new file named `WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx`. \n\nPaste the following code snippet in the file:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx\n*/\nimport React from \"react\";\n\nconst WindTurbineHomePage = () => {\n   return <h1>Hello, World!</h1>;\n};\n\nexport default WindTurbineHomePage;","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"-----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Part 2: Create a route","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Now that we have the `WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx` created, we need to tell the framework when to render the page by specifying a route.\n\nApplication routes are stored in <a href=\"../../metadata/UiSdlRoute/UiRoute.csv\"><code>metadata/UiSdlRoute/UiRoute.csv</code></a>, where you specify the pages for specific URL paths. Add the following rows to `UiRoute.csv`:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"plaintext","value":"# Paste in `metadata/UISdlRoute/UiRoute.csv`\n\nWindTurbine,HomePage,/windturbine,/windturbine\nWindTurbine,HomePage,/,/w","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"This configuration tells the framework to render `WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx`, and the associated route will be either the root URL of your application `/` or accessible via `/windturbine`.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"-----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Part 3: Preview your new page","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"In this section, you learn how to bundle your application UI. ","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### What is the UI Bundler?","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"The UI bundler compiles all of your front end code and backend code and installs any additional dependencies we have defined under `ImplLanguage.Runtime`. This ensures your UI has access to all necessary libraries, C3 AI Types, and methods defined in your package. It will also throw any errors if your code contains any issues.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Start Bundling","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"To start the UI bundler, select the C3 AI icon in the left sidebar to open the extension. In the Applications tab, right-click the application name and select **Start UI Bundling**.\n\n<img src=\"../../src/doc/img/lesson-2/start-bundling.png\" width=\"350px\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n\nOnce bundling is complete, a notification in the bottom right corner displays a link. Select the link to view the bundled UI. It should direct you to the root URL of your application.\n\nYou should see \"Hello, World!\" displayed on the page, like in the following image:\n\n<img src=\"../../src/doc/img/lesson-2/hello-world.png\" width=\"350px\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"-----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Part 4: Add a map to your homepage","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Now that we've covered the basics of creating pages and bundling your UI, let's add a map to the home page. In the setup notebook, we installed Leaflet, which we will use to add a map. \n\nReplace the code in <a href=\"../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx\"><code>WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx</code></a> with the following code snippet. ","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n    WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx\n    This is the main page component for the Wind Turbine application. It renders a map using Leaflet.\n*/\nimport React from 'react';\nimport { MapContainer, TileLayer, ZoomControl } from 'react-leaflet';\nimport 'leaflet/dist/leaflet.css';\nimport '@c3/ui/WindTurbine.scss'; // Custom styles for this application\n\nconst WindTurbineHomePage = () => {\n  return (\n    <>\n        <MapContainer \n            center={[39.8, -98.5]} \n            zoom={4} \n            className=\"map-container\" \n            zoomControl={false} \n            attributionControl={true}\n            {...{} as any} // This avoids the prop warning for using an older version of React \n        >\n            <ZoomControl position=\"bottomleft\" />\n\n            {/* OpenStreetMap Tile Layer */}\n            <TileLayer\n                url=\"https://{s}.basemaps.cartocdn.com/light_all/{z}/{x}/{y}{r}.png\"\n                attribution='&copy; <a href=\"https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright\">OpenStreetMap</a> contributors &copy; <a href=\"https://carto.com/attributions\">CARTO</a>'\n                    {...{} as any}\n            />\n        </MapContainer>\n    </>\n  );\n};\n\nexport default WindTurbineHomePage;","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Before you start the next lab, refresh your bundled UI and verify that the map appears. It should look something like the following:\n\n<img src=\"../../src/doc/img/lesson-2/map.png\" width=\"550px\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Restart UI Bundling","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Refreshing your browser window should rebundle the UI. If it doesn't, you can stop bundling by right-clicking your application name in the **Applications** panel and selecting **Stop UI Bundling**. You can then start UI bundling again. \n\n<img src=\"../../src/doc/img/lesson-2/stop-bundling.png\" width=\"350px\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"-----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Summary\nYou created a home page, registered routes, bundled the UI, and rendered a Leaflet map, establishing the core page and navigation flow.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"<div style=\"display:flex; justify-content:space-between; gap:16px; margin-top:24px; align-items:center; width:100%;\">\n  <a href=\"./01-import-libraries.c3nb\"\n     aria-label=\"Go to Lesson 0: Import Libraries\"\n     style=\"display:inline-flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; padding:10px 16px; border-radius:10px; text-decoration:none; font-weight:600; border:1px solid #d0d7de; background:#f6f8fa; color:#0b1026; box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.06); transition:transform .15s ease, box-shadow .15s ease;\">\n    ← Previous: Import Libraries\n  </a>\n  <a href=\"./03-fetch-turbine-data.c3nb\"\n     aria-label=\"Go to Lesson 2: Fetch Turbine Data\"\n     style=\"display:inline-flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; padding:10px 16px; border-radius:10px; text-decoration:none; font-weight:600; border:1px solid #1f6feb; background:#1f6feb; color:#ffffff; box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.06); transition:transform .15s ease, box-shadow .15s ease;\">\n    Next: Fetch Turbine Data →\n  </a>\n</div>","output":[],"executionSummary":{}}],"metadata":{"id":"9824f0a8-f1a3-4d9f-ae42-70d0f84bc31f","serializerVersion":"1","runtime":"js-rhino"}}